I know what it's like to be in that sort of a relationship, but the way I thought about it was that it was neccessary for my growth, and development.  Everyone needs those bad expiriences, as painfull as they may be, to learn more about themselves.  The point though is that they learn about themselves.  Parents would like to protect us from all the hurt in the world, but it's just not possible.  It's not about living a soap opera, even though at times my life has felt like one, it's about learning how to be an adult.  When our parents were young it was easier for them. There were  identifiable roles that each sex played.  Now we are growing up in a time where there are no rules, and no garountees.  It's hard to have a relationship, and it's hard to be in control when you don't know what that is, and parents all too often just say &quot; No, don't do &quot;.  So much is placed on us, and so much is expected of us that when we come up against these walls of No's we want to break through and find out why, even though for some of us on the other side of the wall there is nothing but a black pit.  It is about controll.  It's what we want, even if we don't know that you need responsibility and sense to use it correctly.  It's like a kid with a gun.  They want to be grown up, and strong like the cowboy they see on t.v., but they don't realize that the gun comes with pain.  Sometimes they, like us, don't realize that you might not get a second chance.    
